  "prompt": "What are the best Shahrukh khan movies?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has had an illustrious career with numerous successful films. Here are some of his most acclaimed movies:\n\n1. **Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge (1995)** - This classic romantic drama is one of the most iconic Bollywood films, known for its timeless love story.\n\n2. **Kuch Kuch Hota Hai (1998)** - A romantic comedy-drama that has become a cult favorite, focusing on friendship, love, and college life.\n\n3. **Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham (2001)** - A multi-starrer family drama that explores themes of family values, traditions, and reconciliation.\n\n4. **My Name Is Khan (2010)** - A powerful drama that addresses issues of identity and race in post-9/11 America, showcasing Shah Rukh's acting prowess.\n\n5. **Devdas (2002)** - A visually stunning adaptation of the classic Indian novel, with SRK delivering a memorable performance as the tragic protagonist.\n\n6. **Chak De! India (2007)** - An inspiring sports drama where Shah Rukh plays a former hockey player turned coach, emphasizing themes of patriotism and leadership.\n\n7. **Swades (2004)** - A thought-provoking film about an NRI's journey to rediscover his roots in rural India, celebrated for its realistic portrayal and emotional depth.\n\n8. **Darr (1993)** - A psychological thriller where Shah Rukh's portrayal of an obsessive lover is both chilling and compelling.\n\n9. **Baazigar (1993)** - A suspense thriller that established SRK as an actor willing to experiment with negative roles early in his career.\n\n10. **Kal Ho Naa Ho (2003)** - A romantic drama that tugs at the heartstrings, known for its emotional depth and soulful music.\n\nThese films highlight Shah Rukh Khan's versatility and his ability to excel in a variety of genres, from romance to drama and beyond.",
